@chooseresidents
    *say
        You can finally afford a place of your own! Now where to live? You've narrowed it down to three locations: out in the beautiful country side, right in the busy city or just outside the city in a cozy suburban home. Which will it be?
    *then
        hear country, live out in the country, in the country, the country{
        decrease money by 70,000
        -> country
        }
        hear city, big city, live in the city, in the city, , the city{
        decrease money by 150,000
        -> city
        }
        hear suburb, suburbs, in the suburbs, the suburbs{
        decrease money by 120,000
        -> suburb
        }
        
@country
    *say
        You love the wide-open outdoors with no traffic, few neighbors, and plenty of room for activiies. The country is where you want to live.
        
    *then
        roll 1d4
            if rollResult == 1{
            ->scenario2
            }
    -> marriage
    

@city
    *say
        You enjoy the hustle and bustle of the City. There are many things to do and go see in the city, that is why you wanted to live there
    *then
     roll 1d4
            if rollResult == 1{
            ->scenario2
            }
    -> marriage

@suburb
    *say
        After looking at all the different places to live you decided being in a safe and cozy suburb would be great for you.
    *then
     roll 1d4
            if rollResult == 1{
            ->scenario2
            }
    -> marriage
    
@marriage
    *say
        Having finally got your job and living on your own, you wonder to yourself if you want to get a spouse to spend your time with. Do you want to get married or stay single?
    *then
        hear married, get married, marry{
        -> married
        }
        hear single, stay single, be alone{
        -> single
        }
        
@married
    *say
    Congratulations! You are getting married to the love of your life. Is the wedding going to be a big one or small?
    *then
        hear big, big wedding, big one{
        decrease money by 40,000
        increase character by 6
        -> big
        }
        hear small, small one, small wedding{
        decrease money by 20,000
        increase character by 3
        -> small
        }
    
@single
    *say
        You figured that getting married would be a waste of your time and cause you pain and suffering. There is a reason why so many people get divorced. You made it through your life. making it through college and having a sucessful job. You live your retirement alone, but it does not feel that way living in the where you are. Congratulations, on completing your Journey! Come back soon and play again.
    *then
        -> retire_choice


@big
    *say
        You want to have a big wedding with lots of people, food, and decorations. The wedding went great. You invited all your family and friends to celebrate the occasion.
    *then
    -> married_life
@small
    *say
        You only wanted to have a few people at your wedding and not many decorations to keep the cost down.
    *then
    -> married_life

@married_life
    *say 
        Now that you have been married for some time and life is going well are kids something you would like to have?
    *then
        hear have kids, yes, want kids, try to have kids{
            roll 1d20
                if rollResult == 5{
                set kids to 3
                -> kids3
                }
                if rollResult <= 4{
                set kids to 2
                -> kids2
                }
                if rollResult >= 6{
                set kids to 1
                -> kids1
                }
        -> kids3
        }
        hear don't have kids, no, no kids, don't want kids{
        -> retire_choice
        }
        
@kids1
    *say 
        You and yoru partner had a kid! Congrats!
    
    *then
        decrease money by 40,000
        increase character by 3
        roll 1d4
            if rollResult ==1{
            ->scenario4
            }
        -> retire_choice
        
@kids2
    *say 
        You and your partner had twins! Twice as much fun!
    
    *then
        decrease money by 80,000
        increase character by 6
        roll 1d4
            if rollResult ==1{
            ->scenario4
            }
        -> retire_choice
        
@kids3
    *say 
        What luck! You and your partner had triplets! A tripple threat!
    
    *then
        decrease money by 120,000
        increase character by 9
        roll 1d4
            if rollResult ==1{
            ->scenario4
            }
        -> retire_choice

@retire_choice
    *say
        You lived a great life having kids and watching them grow up. You have been at your job for 20 years, would you like to retire?
    *then
        hear yes, retire, retire from work {
        -> retire
        }
        hear no, keep working{
        ->dontretire
        }
        
@retire
    *say
        After a great long time at your job, living with your family and seeing them grow up. You decided to reitre from work and enjoy the rest of life together with your spouse. Thank you for playing life, come back again soon.
    *then
        -> stop

@dontretire
    *say
        You enjoy your job to much and don't know if you would ever stop working in life. You continue the rest of your life working with fewer hours and spending the evening with your family. Congratualtions on making through life. Play again and choose different outcomes.
    *then
        -> stop
        
@scenario2
    *say
        You have now moved into your new place but you soon discover that your new living space needs repairs. Thats gonna hurt the wallet!
    *then
        decrease money by 5,000
        -> marriage
        
@scenario1
*say
     You were at a party and fell off a roof and broke your back! You had to be transported by ambulance to the hospital
*then
    decrease money by 10,000
    -> workstudy
    
@scenario3
    *say
        Your hard work has finally paid off! Your boss has decided to give you a raise after all the time and effort you have put in!
    *then
        increase money by $5,000
        -> chooseresidents
        
@scenario4
    *say
        Uh Oh! Looks like your kids have outgrown their current bedset in their room and they need a new one!
    *then
        decrease money by 1000
        -> retire_choice